1|Greed or Glory: PCs hear about a dungeon nearby and how no one dares to enter it.
1|Raiding Monsters: Monsters or evil humanoids attack farmsteads and must be stopped.
1|Treasure Hunt: An NPC has a treasure map.
1|Guards: PCs hired to protect merchant caravan through dangerous terrain.
1|Seek: Locate missing important NPC.
1|Destroy: Purge a dungeon of monsters.
1|Underwater Exploration: Map area of sea and explore island of suitable settling areas.
1|Mine: Search underground for rich vein of ore or a legendary cache of gems.
1|Protect: Enhance village defenses and train locals to defend themselves from an impending threat.
1|Ruins Stir: Secret but good NPCs are searching for holy relic and accidentally stir up undead.
1|Spies: The PCs are hired to collect information on a nearby group or kingdom.
1|Investigate: PCs brought in to solve a crime.
1|Bait and Switch: Monster far beyond the PCs is allegedly behind the plot - can this be true?
1|Sacrilege: Confront zealots allegedly carryng out human sacrifices.
1|Salvage: The crew of a listing merchang ship row ashore claiming that somehow their cargo scuttled the vessel, and that they want nothing more to do with it.
1|Steal: Work for good-fronted merchant group to steal an object they stole in the first place.
1|Capture: A rival merchant or guild wishes monster intact to serve as guard.
1|Escape: During routine adventure PCs are trapped by a rockfall which unleashes horror.
1|Roundup: A rancher needs extra hands to protect his herd from rustlers as he heads to the market.
1|Execution: The PCs or any ally face a harsh punishment for breaking an unjust or arbitrary law.
1|Exploration: The PCs quest to explore a new realm, whether it be a continent, underground expanse, plane, or other locale.
1|Kinslayer: A relative of the ruler plans to claim the throne for his or her own.
1|Watch: PCs hired by town watch to uncover spies.
1|On the Run: The PCs must help a goodly creature escape those who hunt it.
1|Monstrous: The locals decide the newly arrived PCs are behind the deaths.
1|Alliance: Prevent a marriage intended to unite two monster clans without them realizing the sabotage.
1|Precious Cargo: Someone must keep a monster's egg safe until it hatches.
1|Dead Man Walking: A long-dead ally or personality reappears, seemingly alive and unharmed.
1|Chainbreaker: Find the slaver's base by getting captured and then escape to get reinforcements.
1|A Little Knowledge: Someone keeps trying to kill the hapless storyteller; which of his tall tales is actually true?
1|Unexpected Event: Earthquake or volcano unleashes horrors onto countryside or settlement.
1|Reagent: A powerfull magic user needs the PCs' help in tracking down a rare component or ingredient.
1|Menagerie: Creatures have escaped from a private collection and the PCs are hired to return them.
1|Courteous Killer: An assassin sends a letter suggesting that the target put his affairs in order.
1|Plague Run: Find the ingredients that cure the disease and get them back before too many more people die.
1|Deadly Waters: The river has turned black and toxic - what's going on upstream?
1|Feathered Apocalypse: All the birds are dying and the druids are looking for someone to blame.
1|Prophecy: A prophecy is due for fulfillment. The PCs must work to fulfill or prevent it.
1|Animal Enemies: All the usually peaceful animals become killers.
1|Political: PCs assist local leaders in rooting out evil in their own halls.
1|Festival: PCs infiltrate performers to uncover a killer.
1|From Beyond: PCs must prevent plot to summon a powerful outsider.
1|Incursion: Creatures from another plane infest town and take hostages to experiment upon.
1|Revenant: Do the PCs stand in the way of an evil avenging spirit intent on wiping out an entire family?
1|The Strange Child: Is the changeling really behind the nightmares like the locals say?
1|Doppelganger: The PCs or others are seen murdering and stealing and the locals went revenge.
1|Righteous Indignation: A local tribe of non-evil monsters threatens a community that has trespassed upon their land or otherwise offended them.
1|Surrounded: PCs find themselves hunted in wilderness. Can they escape and survive?
1|Hunted: For some reason everyone thinks the PCs are someone they aren't. As the city mobilizes to capture and execute them can the PCs get to the bottom of the plot?
1|Dragon: A dragon appears in a city and demands tribute. Can the PCs defeat it? Is it real?
